createLimitOrder(uint256,uint256,uint256.details: Creates a limit order Requirements: - in case of sell: msg.sender has to have sufficient shares available for selling - in case of buy: msg.sender has to have sufficient ETH deposited The relevant hooks are called: _onOrderUpsert, _onSharesReservedChange, _onEthReservedBalanceChange

createMarketOrder(uint256,uint256,uint8).details: Creates a market order and executes against the registered limit orders Requirements: - in case of sell: msg.sender has to have sufficient shares available for selling - in case of buy: msg.sender has to have sufficient ETH deposited The relevant hooks are called: _onTradeExecution, _onOrderUpsert, _onSharesReservedChange, _onEthReservedBalanceChange, _onEthBalanceChange

getEthBalance(address).details: returns the ETH balance of the owner

getEthReserveBalance(address).details: returns the ETH reserved balance of the owner

getOrders(uint256,uint8).details: returns the orders of the token and side

getSharesReserveBalance(address,uint256).details: returns the shares reserved in orders for a given owner and tokenId

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawEth(uint256).details: Withdraw ETH Requirements: - msg.sender has to have equal or more ETH than the amount to withdraw
